    <id>http://leetschau.github.io/blog/2014/08/17/hello-world</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1>Install</h1>

<p>Ref: <a href="http://octopress.org/docs/setup/">Octopress Setup</a>.</p>

<pre><code>curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby
rvm install 1.9.3
rvm use 1.9.3
rvm rubygems latest
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.13.1/install.sh | bash      // install [nvm](https://github.com/creationix/nvm)
echo "source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh" &gt;&gt; ~/.zshrc
nvm install 0.10
nvm use 0.10
cd ~/apps
git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git octopress
cd octopress
gem install bundler
bundle install
rake install
</code></pre>

<p>Note: Do NOT use ruby 2.1.1, it can&rsquo;t install bundler, while ruby 2.1.2 is OK.</p>

<h1>Usage</h1>

<h2>Setup</h2>

<ol>
<li><p>Create a new repo named &ldquo;leetschau.github.io&rdquo; on <a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a>;</p></li>
<li><p>Run following commands:</p>

<pre><code> rake setup_github_pages     // when asked, copy the url of above repo
 rake generate               // if it complains no javascript rumtime found, run `source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh`
 rake deploy                 // you need provide username and password of your github account
</code></pre></li>
</ol>


<h2>Configuration</h2>

<p>Modify _config.yml to customize blog&rsquo;s title, subtitle, author and blog descriptions.</p>

<p>Under &ldquo;3rd Party Settings&rdquo;, set &ldquo;github_user&rdquo; as &ldquo;leetschau&rdquo;.</p>

<h2>Post new blog</h2>

<p>Run the following command to create a new post, and edit post content:</p>

<pre><code>rake new_post["Hello World"]
vi source/_posts/2014-08-18-hello-world.markdown
</code></pre>

<h2>Preview new blog</h2>

<p>Run the following command to generate new post and preview them:</p>

<pre><code>rake generate
rake watch
rake preview
</code></pre>
